The Typeof Type Operator

When used in a type context, `typeof` captures the type of a variable or expression.

### Basic Type Extraction

```typescript
const user = {
  name: "Alice",
  age: 30,
  isActive: true
};

type UserType = typeof user;
// { name: string; age: number; isActive: boolean }

const newUser: UserType = {
  name: "Bob",
  age: 25,
  isActive: false
};
```

### typeof with Primitive Values

```typescript
const greeting = "Hello";
type Greeting = typeof greeting; // "Hello" (literal type)

const count = 42;
type Count = typeof count; // number (widened)

const flag = true as const;
type Flag = typeof flag; // true (literal)
```

### typeof with Functions

```typescript
function add(a: number, b: number): number {
  return a + b;
}

type AddFn = typeof add;
// (a: number, b: number) => number

const multiply: typeof add = (x, y) => x * y;
// Works because signatures are compatible
```

### typeof with Class

```typescript
class Point {
  constructor(public x: number, public y: number) {}
}

type PointClass = typeof Point;
// new (x: number, y: number) => Point
```

### Combination Pattern

```typescript
const config = {
  api: { baseUrl: "https://api.example.com", version: "v2" },
  auth: { tokenKey: "access_token", refreshInterval: 3600000 }
} as const;

type Config = typeof config;
type ApiConfig = Config["api"];
type AuthConfig = Config["auth"];
```

> **Key Point:** Use `typeof` in type context to extract and reuse types from existing values.

codeExample:
// Extract type from API response shape
const apiResponse = {
  status: 200 as const,
  data: { id: 1, name: "Alice" },
  meta: { page: 1, total: 10 }
};

type ApiResponse = typeof apiResponse;
type ResponseData = ApiResponse["data"];

// Reuse type from a library function
import { createStore } from "redux";
const store = createStore((state: any) => state);
type Store = typeof store;
// Extracts the full store type

// Type from enum-like object
const HttpStatus = {
  OK: 200,
  NOT_FOUND: 404,
  ERROR: 500
} as const;

type HttpStatusValues = (typeof HttpStatus)[keyof typeof HttpStatus];
// 200 | 404 | 500
